  KEY INSIGHTS (ARM64-specific):
  • Dominant stage: Copy (39.7% of total)
  • Copy/Unmap = 1.1×  → DMA offloading is highest priority
  • Lock: CV=0.98 (moderate) — TLBI broadcast timing variation
  • Copy: CV=1.77 (high) — likely cache-line bouncing on ARM64 exclusive pair (LDAXR/STXR) or scheduler jitter
  • Remap: CV=0.56 (moderate) — TLBI broadcast timing variation
  • Unlock: CV=0.87 (moderate) — TLBI broadcast timing variation
  • Lock contention: none — all uncontended (fast LDAXR/STXR path)
  • Unmap mean=0.4µs, P95=0.6µs
    ARM64: cost = rmap walk + TLBI VAE1IS + DSB ISH per PTE

  TRY_TO_MIGRATE BREAKDOWN — 4KB (timing_4kb_512.csv)
  Component                                Mean       P95  % of unmap
  ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
  try_to_migrate() [rmap+TLBI+DSB]         0.40      0.54       91.6%
  surrounding overhead (fixed)             0.04                  8.4%
  Stage 2 total (unmap_ns)                 0.43                100.0%

  TLB BATCHING IMPLICATION:
  • try_to_migrate() is 91.6% of Stage 2
  • This is the portion that scales with mapcount (O(N) DSB ISH stalls)
  • Fixed overhead (0.04 µs) is irreducible regardless of strategy
  • Batching reduces DSB ISH from N stalls to 1 stall per migration
