  LINEAR REGRESSION (cost = α×degree + β):
    Unmap:  α=  1.45 µs/process,  β=  0.35 µs  (per-TLBI + rmap walk cost)
    Remap:  α=  0.36 µs/process,  β= -0.35 µs  (per-PTE write cost)

  ARM64 TLBI INTERPRETATION:
    Per-process TLBI overhead ≈ 1.45 µs
    This is TLBI VAE1IS + DSB ISH per PTE mapping.
    Batching N shootdowns into one TLBI range instruction
    would reduce Stage 2 cost toward the β=0.35 µs baseline.
